SSH : secure shell 
Network Communication Protocol for devices
Default Port = 22
Other Alternatives Port : 1024 to 32767

Syntax {
    ssh UserName@IP 

    OR

    ssh UserName@HostName
}

 
ssh -V : check Present SSH version
sudo apt install openssh-server : install SSH
/etc/ssh/sshd_config : File Contain Info About SSH

systemctl status ssh : check if ssh active
systemctl start ssh : start ssh service
systemctl stop ssh : stop ssh service

PassWordLess SSH {
    ssh-keygen : generate ssh key : pair of public and private

    ssh-copy-id -i /PATH/sshkeys.pub UserName@IP : copy key to other server


}



